* The interface that must be implemented by all selectors * that can be used from {@link MessageFormatter}. * *

Selectors are used to choose between different message variants, * similar to plural, selectordinal, * and select in {@link android.icu.text.MessageFormat}.

* * @deprecated This API is for technology preview only. * @hide Only a subset of ICU is exposed in Android * @hide draft / provisional / internal are hidden on Android

methods.name: List<String> matches(Object value, List<String> keys, Map<String, Object> variableOptions)
methods.comment:
* A method that is invoked for the object to match and each key. * *

For example an English plural {@code matches} would return {@code true} * for {@code matches(1, "1")}, {@code matches(1, "one")}, and {@code matches(1, "*")}.

* * @param value the value to select on. * @param keys the key to test for matching. * @param variableOptions options that are not know at build time. * @return the formatted string. * * @deprecated This API is for technology preview only. * @hide draft / provisional / internal are hidden on Android

methodNames: List<String> matches(Object value, List<String> keys, Map<String, Object> variableOptions)
